## JSX Expressiveness Rules
- NEVER forget the expressiveness and readability of JSX
- JSX provides clear, hierarchical structure that is easy to understand
- Tagged Templates should create JSX, NOT generate LaTeX directly
- The goal is to write LaTeX using JSX syntax for better readability
- Maintain the JSX â†’ LaTeX transformation pipeline for expressiveness
- JSX allows for nested structures, props, and dynamic content with composing components in a readable way

## Testing Rules
- ALWAYS write tests when adding new features to ensure nothing breaks
- Run existing tests after any code changes to verify functionality
- Create snapshot tests for new components to ensure consistent output
- Test edge cases and error scenarios for robust functionality

## Development Standards
Use JSX whenever possible, but keep the original React.createElement version for the index.js file. Use uppercase first letter for the components name.

